Let X be a scheme (or an algebraic space) of finite type over \mathbb {C}, and assume it to be separated.
    Then there exists a diagram

    2364hodge-theory-iii-8.2.1.1hodge-theory-iii-8.2.1.1.xmlEquation8.2.1.1         X         \xleftarrow {\alpha } Y_\bullet          \hookrightarrow  \overline {Y}_\bullet        \tag{8.2.1.1}       

    in which Y_\bullet  is the complement of a normal crossing divisor in a smooth and proper simplicial scheme \overline {Y}_\bullet , and is a proper hypercover of X.
    We have ((II) of )

    2365hodge-theory-iii-8.2.1.2hodge-theory-iii-8.2.1.2.xmlEquation8.2.1.2         \operatorname {H}^\bullet (X)         \xrightarrow {\sim } \operatorname {H}^\bullet (Y_\bullet ).       \tag{8.2.1.2}

